y and folklore that detail life before the reservation period and a biographical sketch of the Uhlenbecks, featuring aspects of C.C. Uhlenbeck's career as a linguist and scholar, as well as numerous photographs from the era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnthropologistszMontanavBiography. 0aAnthropologists' spouseszMontanavDiaries. 0aLinguistszMontanavBiography. 0aPiegan IndianszMontana. 0aSiksika Indians. 0aSiksika languagevTextsvTranslations into English. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh1 aBerkel, Klaas van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggermont-Molenaar, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggermont-Molenaar, Mary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGenee, Inge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehoe, Alice B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehoe, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUhlenbeck, Mr. C. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Josselin de Jong, J.P.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552384060?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552384060423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552384060/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles